                        <h2>Shannon Ratchet</h2>
                        <p>We use the Shannon Ratchet trading strategy in this application. The Shannon Ratchet trading strategy keeps exactly the same market value in the stock and the cash, buying and selling stocks to do so. Claude Shannon proposed this strategy in response to the "efficient market hypothesis", which argues that since markets already incorporate all information into prices, the prices must be efficient and thus the price of a stock is really a random walk. Ratchet converts volatility in the walks into gains, utilizing unpredictability.</p>
